---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Mission" description="Learn about the Lac Qui Parle Lake Association's mission to preserve Minnesota's premier walleye fishery.">
  <section class="bg-lake-900 py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl">Our Mission</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-lake-200">Dedicated to the betterment of Lac Qui Parle Lake and the outdoor enthusiasts who enjoy it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-lake max-w-none">
        <p>
          The Lac Qui Parle Lake Association was created in <strong>1982</strong> as a non-profit organization dedicated to the betterment of Lac Qui Parle Lake. Walleye and waterfowl are two things that come to mind when outdoorsmen around Minnesota hear the words Lac Qui Parle Lake.
        </p>

        <p>
          Lac Qui Parle has a tradition of being one of the best walleye fisheries in the state, and the Lac Qui Parle Lake Association is helping in keeping that tradition alive for the anglers of Minnesota.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Do</h2>
        <p>
          Since its inception, the Lac Qui Parle Lake Association has been involved in funding numerous lake projects as well as projects that help aid the outdoor enthusiast. The Association works in conjunction with the <strong>Minnesota DNR</strong> and has been instrumental in providing funding for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Walleye stocking programs</li>
          <li>Fishing piers</li>
          <li>Boat ramps</li>
          <li>Rip rap projects on erodible shorelines</li>
          <li>Youth fishing activities</li>
          <li>Community partnerships like Tri-County Let's Go Fishing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Board of Directors</h2>
        <p>Our dedicated board members volunteer their time to ensure the continued health and enjoyment of Lac Qui Parle Lake:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Scott Monson</li>
          <li>Steve Mitlyng</li>
          <li>Joe Bungarden</li>
          <li>Pete McGinty</li>
          <li>Andy Johnson</li>
          <li>Brett Jacobs</li>
          <li>Gary Groothius</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Get Involved</h2>
        <p>
          The best way to support Lac Qui Parle Lake is to <a href="/membership">become a member</a>. Annual dues are just $10, and your contributions go directly toward lake improvement projects and conservation efforts.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contact the LQP Lake Association at:<br />
          <strong>PO Box 66, Montevideo, MN 56265</strong><br />
          <a href="mailto:minnkotatackle@yahoo.com">minnkotatackle@yahoo.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
